ch for small-scale coronal\nturbulence and remote sensing of the structure of CMEs. Future investigations\nwith the Expanded Very Large Array (EVLA) or Murchison Widefield Array (MWA)\ncould provide unique observational input on the astrophysics of CMEs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 26 Sep 2008 14:33:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
